At Client, we are committed to delivering a best in class experience in all aspects of our business. The Logistics Team is no exception. Client Electronics America’s Mobile Logistics Team is responsible for ensuring cost efficient, on time product delivery to our customers, to meet forecasted demand by the Sales Subsidiary. To accomplish this objective, Logistics collaborates with Sales Teams, Marketing Teams, and with the Client Global Operations Center. Information is managed using spreadsheets, email, SAP, and Client Systems and Tools. The Logistics Claims and Loss Prevention Analyst will be responsible for analyzing claims and loss data, cataloging, slicing and dicing the data to locate trends and patterns. Regular communication with the operations team will be necessary to understand daily processes and identify where the process gaps and risk pockets are in the operation. This position requires a high level of interaction with a broad number of employees to validate data and collaborate on our findings. Ultimately, the goal of the Analyst is to drive out losses and eliminate claims through targeted process improvements and best in class benchmarking. This position is critical to the Logistics department: as an operational department with time sensitive daily executables needed to deliver products to customers, the Claims and Loss Prevention Analyst must study the loss patterns and ratios and make recommendations that drive a reduction in losses year over year. To accomplish this objective, Logistics collaborates with Sales Teams, Marketing Teams, and with the Client Global Operations Center. Information is managed using spreadsheets, email, SAP, and Client Systems and Tools. The Logistics Claims and Loss Prevention Analyst will be responsible for analyzing claims and loss data, cataloging, slicing and dicing the data to locate trends and patterns. Regular communication with the operations team will be necessary to understand daily processes and identify where the process gaps and risk pockets are in the operation. This position requires a high level of interaction with a broad number of employees to validate data and collaborate on our findings. Ultimately, the goal of the Analyst is to drive out losses and eliminate claims through targeted process improvements and best in class benchmarking. This position is critical to the Logistics department: as an operational department with time sensitive daily executables needed to deliver products to customers, the Claims and Loss Prevention Analyst must study the loss patterns and ratios and make recommendations that drive a reduction in losses year over year. The Logistics Claims and Loss Prevention Analyst will report to the Claims Manager.
